  <div class="section-number">01 — About this project</div>
  <div class="section-title">What is this?</div>
  <div class="dark-box">
    <h3>The Google UX Design Certificate</h3>
    <p>The Google UX Design Certificate on Coursera is a structured, end-to-end UX programme that covers the full design process — from initial user research and problem definition through to high-fidelity prototyping and usability testing.</p>
    <p>Each phase produces real deliverables: user personas, journey maps, wireframes, prototypes, and usability test reports. The programme follows the same process used by professional UX designers.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section-number" style="margin-top: 56px;">02 — The UX Process</div>
  <div class="section-title">Five phases, end to end</div>
  <div class="process-grid">
    <div class="process-step active">
      <div class="check">✓</div>
