  <div class="section-number">03 — What the project covers</div>
  <div class="section-title">Key deliverables</div>
  <div class="deliverables-list">
    <div class="deliverable-row">
      <div class="icon">🔍</div>
      <div>
        <h4>User Research</h4>
        <p>Interviews, empathy maps, and user personas grounded in real observations — not assumptions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="deliverable-row">
      <div class="icon">🗺</div>
      <div>
        <h4>Problem Definition</h4>
        <p>Problem statement and user journey map that frames the design challenge around actual user needs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="deliverable-row">
      <div class="icon">✏️</div>
      <div>
        <h4>Wireframes & Low-fi Prototype</h4>
        <p>Paper sketches and low-fidelity digital wireframes that test the structure before any visual design begins.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="deliverable-row">
      <div class="icon">🎨</div>
      <div>
        <h4>High-Fidelity Design in Figma</h4>
        <p>A complete high-fidelity prototype in Figma with a defined visual system, component library, and interaction flows.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="deliverable-row">
      <div class="icon">🧪</div>
      <div>
        <h4>Usability Testing</h4>
        <p>Moderated usability tests with real participants, documented findings, and design iterations based on what was learned.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="page page-break">
  <div class="section-number">04 — Why this matters</div>
  <div class="section-title">What this project shows</div>
  <div class="timeline">
    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-dot">📐</div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <div class="timeline-tag">Process</div>
        <h4>Following the full UX process, not just the output</h4>
        <p>A lot of portfolios show finished screens. This project documents the entire process — the messy research, the wrong turns, the iterations — because that is where UX skill actually lives.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-dot">🧠</div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <div class="timeline-tag">Thinking</div>
        <h4>Design decisions grounded in evidence</h4>
        <p>Every design decision in this project is linked back to what was learned from users — not aesthetic preference, not convention. Research first, design second.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-dot">🔁</div>
      <div class="timeline-content">
        <div class="timeline-tag">Iteration</div>
        <h4>Testing and changing, not just testing</h4>
        <p>Usability testing is only useful if you act on what you find. This project documents what broke, what was changed, and why — because that is how design actually improves.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="coming-soon">
